Every time the first ActionListener runs, it calls `tab0Layout()` adding a *new* ActionListener to the t0Test variable, and likewise, every time the second ActionListener runs, it calls `tab1Layout()` adding a *new* ActionListener to the t1Test variable. This means, that each ActionListener adds a new copy of itself to its own button which each call, and this causes a bunch of listeners to be added to buttons, all calling at the same time. Not good.

